# go clean -modcache
# go clean -cache

What to include in the README?
I recommend adding a "Prerequisites" table at the top of your file:

Tool	Version	Purpose

Go	1.25.8+	Core logic and compilation
Android SDK	API 24+	Android system integration
Android NDK	r25b or newer	Cross-compiling Go for ARM64
Java (JDK)	17	Required by Gradle/Android Studio


 - go installation

1. Download and Extract

# 1. Download the official Linux binary
wget https://go.dev/dl/go1.25.8.linux-amd64.tar.gz

# 2. Remove any previous installation and extract the new one to /usr/local
# (You will likely need sudo for this)
sudo rm -rf /usr/local/go && sudo tar -C /usr/local -xzf go1.25.8.linux-amd64.tar.gz

2. Update your Environment
# Add these lines to your ~/.bashrc
export GOROOT=/usr/local/go
export GOPATH=$HOME/go
export PATH=$PATH:$GOROOT/bin:$GOPATH/bin

 - dowloading prerequisite packages

go get github.com/net2share/vaydns@v0.2.6
go get github.com/xjasonlyu/tun2socks/v2@v2.6.0
go mod tidy

 - gomobile and gobind installation
Build Requirements
To compile the Android VPN library, you must have the gomobile and gobind toolsets installed and synchronized with your current Go toolchain.

1. Install/Update Mobile Tools
Instead of using a global installation, we recommend building the tools from within the project directory. This ensures the tools use the exact same Go version and dependency logic as your VPN code.

# Add the mobile tools to your local module tracking
go get golang.org/x/mobile/cmd/gomobile
go get golang.org/x/mobile/cmd/gobind

# Build the binaries into your Go bin folder
go build -o $(go env GOPATH)/bin/gobind golang.org/x/mobile/cmd/gobind
go build -o $(go env GOPATH)/bin/gomobile golang.org/x/mobile/cmd/gomobile
gomobile init

gomobile bind -v \
    -target=android/arm64 \
    -androidapi 24 \
    -ldflags="-s -w" \
    -o vaydns-arm64.aar \
    ./mobile
    
cp vaydns-arm64.aar ~/AndroidStudioProjects/vaydns/app/libs/vaydns-arm64.aar    
    
Clean Paths: Using $(go env GOPATH)/bin/ ensures the tools are placed where the shell expects to find them, regardless of whether the user is on Linux, macOS, or WSL.

Troubleshooting Note for the README:
If users encounter the error "golang.org/x/mobile/bind" is not found, advise them to run:


1. Create the tools.go file
Go's dependency management (go mod tidy) often removes packages that aren't directly called by your code. Since golang.org/x/mobile/bind is a support library used only during the build process, we must create a "blank import" to keep it active.

Create a file named tools.go in your project root:


// +build tools

package tools

import (
    _ "golang.org/x/mobile/bind"
    _ "golang.org/x/mobile/cmd/gobind"
    _ "golang.org/x/mobile/cmd/gomobile"
)

2. Sync and Pin Dependencies
Run the following commands to download the necessary metadata and lock the versions in your go.sum:

go get golang.org/x/mobile/bind
go get golang.org/x/mobile/cmd/gobind
go get golang.org/x/mobile/cmd/gomobile
go mod tidy

3. Build Local Tooling

go build -o $(go env GOPATH)/bin/gobind golang.org/x/mobile/cmd/gobind
go build -o $(go env GOPATH)/bin/gomobile golang.org/x/mobile/cmd/gomobile

# Initialize the mobile environment
gomobile init

4. Generate the Android Archive (.aar)
With the environment pinned and the tools built, you can now run the binding command:

gomobile bind -v \
    -target=android/arm64 \
    -androidapi 24 \
    -ldflags="-s -w" \
    -o vaydns-arm64.aar \
    ./mobile
    
    
cp vaydns-arm64.aar ~/AndroidStudioProjects/vaydns/app/libs/vaydns-arm64.aar 

Android Environment Setup
    
To build the .aar file and the final APK, your system needs the Android SDK and NDK.
1. Install the SDK & NDK (Command Line)

# 1. Download command-line tools from official Android site
# 2. Install the specific platform and NDK version
sdkmanager "platforms;android-24" "build-tools;34.0.0" "ndk;26.1.10909125"

2. Set Environment Variables
gomobile needs to know exactly where these tools are located. Add these to your ~/.bashrc:

export ANDROID_HOME=$HOME/Android/Sdk
export ANDROID_NDK_HOME=$ANDROID_HOME/ndk/26.1.10909125 # Match your version
export PATH=$PATH:$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools/latest/bin:$ANDROID_HOME/platform-tools



    
    
